      "test_id_raw": "py/path-injection",
      "test_name_raw": "py/path-injection",
      "judge_verdict": "TP",
      "judge_reason": "The `filename` comes from user-controlled multipart data. `is_valid_filename` allows `.` and `-` but does not block `..` or `/` (not needed since `os.path.join` is used, but filename like `..%2Ffoo.json` after URL decoding or `../foo.json` in the raw multipart would pass validation and lead to directory traversal). The validation only checks alphanumeric + `-_.`, so `../foo.json` passes and `os.path.join` will resolve outside CONFIG_DIR."
    },
    {
      "tool": "codeql",
